s from 5.3.15, it likely already has the scaffold. I see that Spring 6 uses optional dependencies like jakarta.ejb-api instead of javax.ejb, which don't need tests. Adding \\\"jakarta.annotation-api\\\" might help cover the CommonAnnotationBeanPostProcessor. However, optional dependencies could complicate metadata conditions without clear necessity. The set up might require more than just the scaffold for better native coverage, especially since the user requested authoritative local Gradle and Native Image verification. Let’s create a concise JSON summary with the right structure.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker image is indicated; the javac failure is from stale Spring 5.x tests referencing APIs removed from spring-context 6.x, while normal Spring Context usage is in-process.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Generate tests against the Spring 6.0.x API surface and avoid removed Spring 5 remoting/EJB/WebLogic/WebSphere classes such as org.springframework.remoting.*, AbstractSlsbInvokerInterceptor, LocalSlsbInvokerInterceptor, JndiRmiServiceExporter, RemoteInvocation, RmiClientInterceptorUtils, WebLogicLoadTimeWeaver, WebSphereLoadTimeWeaver, and WebSphereMBeanServerFactoryBean. If tests exercise default @Configuration class enhancement/proxyBeanMethods=true in native image, set spring.objenesis.ignore=true for JVM/native test execution and either pre-generate the Spring CGLIB proxy classes before native-image compilation or prefer @Configuration(proxyBeanMethods=false)/GenericApplicationContext tests that avoid runtime CGLIB generation.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Spring Context has many optional integrations; adding tests for Jakarta annotations, EJB, validation, Kotlin, Groovy, AspectJ, or reactive APIs may require targeted optional test dependencies, but they are not required for meaningful core ApplicationContext coverage.\",\n    \"Runtime